@page "/roadmap"

<PageTitle>PureWave | Upgrade Roadmap</PageTitle>

<section class="page-intro roadmap-intro">
    <span class="section-tag">Sample Deliverable</span>
    <h1>The Cinematic Upgrade Roadmap</h1>
    <p>
        This page works a real PureWave-style recommendation into the site: a phased path from a strong front-stage foundation
        to a full 7.4.4 Atmos room. It is based on the report prepared for Revz and shows how PureWave turns ambition into a practical sequence.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="roadmap-summary">
    <div>
        <span class="section-tag">Executive Summary</span>
        <h2>Build the room in phases so every rand improves the final system.</h2>
    </div>

    <p>
        The logic is simple: do not rush into a dozen mediocre speakers. Start with the front stage and AVR foundation, then lock in bass,
        then widen the surround field, and only then chase the Atmos dream. Each phase below includes Budget, Hobby, and Enthusiast tiers.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="roadmap-video-section">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-tag">Video Walkthrough</span>
        <h2>Watch the roadmap explained.</h2>
        <p>
            This video walks through the same phased upgrade logic in a more conversational format, making it easier for clients
            to understand why PureWave recommends sequence before scale.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="roadmap-video-card">
        <video class="roadmap-video" controls preload="metadata" poster="/images/pure-wave-logo.png">
            <source src="/videos/purewave-theatre-roadmap.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
            Your browser does not support embedded video playback.
        </video>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="phase-stack">
    <article class="phase-card">
        <div class="phase-heading">
            <span class="phase-index">Phase 1</span>
            <div>
                <h2>The Front Stage Foundation</h2>
                <p>Build a 3.0 architecture first. Dialogue, panning, and long-term upgrade ceiling are decided here.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tier-grid">
            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Budget</span>
                <h3>Denon AVR-X1800H + Polk Monitor XT Front Stage</h3>
                <p>High-value entry point that gets the room started properly.</p>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li>Denon AVR-X1800H</li>
                    <li>Polk Monitor XT60 towers</li>
                    <li>Polk Monitor XT30 center</li>
                </ul>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R30,000</strong>
            </article>

            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Hobby</span>
                <h3>Denon AVR-X2800H + Monitor Audio Bronze Front Stage</h3>
                <p>The sweet spot for stronger power delivery and more serious listening.</p>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li>Denon AVR-X2800H</li>
                    <li>Monitor Audio Bronze 200 towers</li>
                    <li>Monitor Audio Bronze C150 center</li>
                </ul>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R47,500</strong>
            </article>

            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Enthusiast</span>
                <h3>Marantz Cinema 50 + Bowers & Wilkins 600 Series</h3>
                <p>Reference-minded foundation with the processing headroom needed for the long game.</p>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li>Marantz Cinema 50</li>
                    <li>Bowers & Wilkins 603 S3 towers</li>
                    <li>Bowers & Wilkins HTM6 S3 center</li>
                </ul>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R121,870</strong>
            </article>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="phase-card">
        <div class="phase-heading">
            <span class="phase-index">Phase 2</span>
            <div>
                <h2>The Low-Frequency Foundation</h2>
                <p>Bass is not an accessory. Dual subwoofers are where the room starts to behave like a cinema.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tier-grid">
            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Budget</span>
                <h3>Single SVS SB-1000 Pro</h3>
                <p>A strong sealed subwoofer that introduces real cinematic impact without blowing up the budget.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R22,790</strong>
            </article>

            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Hobby</span>
                <h3>Dual SVS PB-1000 Pro</h3>
                <p>Two subs smooth out bass response and bring better seat-to-seat consistency.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R64,000</strong>
            </article>

            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Enthusiast</span>
                <h3>Dual SVS PB-3000 or a custom ELF design</h3>
                <p>For clients who want physical low-frequency pressure and room-specific bass architecture.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R94,000 or quoted per custom project</strong>
            </article>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="phase-card">
        <div class="phase-heading">
            <span class="phase-index">Phase 3</span>
            <div>
                <h2>The Surround Envelope</h2>
                <p>Once the front stage and bass are locked in, the room gains width, motion, and immersion.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tier-grid">
            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Budget</span>
                <h3>Polk Monitor XT15 surrounds</h3>
                <p>A practical bookshelf pair for wall mounting or stands.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R4,500</strong>
            </article>

            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Hobby</span>
                <h3>Monitor Audio Bronze 50 surrounds</h3>
                <p>Higher fidelity and better timbre continuity with the Bronze front stage.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R9,500</strong>
            </article>

            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Enthusiast</span>
                <h3>Bowers & Wilkins 606 S3 surrounds</h3>
                <p>A more resolving surround speaker for a room already chasing reference-grade presentation.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R22,990</strong>
            </article>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="phase-card">
        <div class="phase-heading">
            <span class="phase-index">Phase 4</span>
            <div>
                <h2>The Atmos Dream</h2>
                <p>Object-based audio only works when the processing and speaker architecture are ready for it.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="roadmap-note">
            <strong>Reality check:</strong> the Budget and Hobby AVRs from Phase 1 cap out earlier. A true 7.4.4 room needs a much stronger processing foundation.
        </div>

        <div class="tier-grid">
            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Budget</span>
                <h3>Polk XT90 Atmos toppers</h3>
                <p>An entry path into Atmos, but still a compromise compared with true overhead channels.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R5,500</strong>
            </article>

            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Hobby</span>
                <h3>4x Monitor Audio C165 in-ceiling speakers</h3>
                <p>Discrete overhead channels for a real Atmos field, typically alongside a stronger AVR path.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R20,000</strong>
            </article>

            <article class="tier-card">
                <span class="plan-accent">Enthusiast</span>
                <h3>Rear surrounds, four in-ceilings, more subs, and external amplification</h3>
                <p>The full theatrical architecture for a serious dedicated room.</p>
                <strong>Estimated total: about R150,000+</strong>
            </article>
        </div>
    </article>
</section>

<section class="comparison-band">
    <div>
        <span class="section-tag">What this shows</span>
        <h2>PureWave does not just recommend products. It sequences decisions.</h2>
    </div>

    <p>
        This kind of roadmap is exactly where The Blueprint and The Director become valuable: aligning budget, room constraints,
        acoustic priorities, and upgrade ambition into a path that still makes sense two phases later.
    </p>

    <a class="button-primary" href="/intake">Start your own brief</a>
</section>
